goals.question: What is the distribution of airports across different states in the USA?
goals.visualization: bar chart of number of airports per state
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the states with the highest and lowest number of airports and can be useful for airlines in planning their routes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airports across different cities?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude of airports
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the cities with the highest and lowest number of airports and can be useful for airlines in planning their routes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports?
goals.visualization: scatter plot of latitude and longitude of airports
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the geographical spread of airports and can be useful for airlines in planning their routes.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airport names?
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the most common airport names and can be useful for airlines in branding and marketing.

goals.question: What is the distribution of airport codes?
goals.rationale: This helps in identifying the most common airport codes and can be useful for airlines in branding and marketing.

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    state_counts = data['state'].value_counts()
    ax = state_counts.plot(kind='bar', figsize=(15, 7), color='c')
    ax.set_xlabel('States')
    ax.set_ylabel('Number of Airports')
    ax.set_title('What is the distribution of airports across different states in the USA?', wrap=True)
    ax.legend(['Number of Airports'])
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    fig, ax = plt.subplots()
    scatter = ax.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'], c=data['state'].cat.codes, cmap='viridis', alpha=0.5)
    ax.set_xlabel('Longitude')
    ax.set_ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airports across different cities?', wrap=True)
    legend1 = ax.legend(*scatter.legend_elements(), title="States", loc="upper left", bbox_to_anchor=(1, 1))
    ax.add_artist(legend1)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.scatter(data['longitude'], data['latitude'])
    plt.xlabel('Longitude')
    plt.ylabel('Latitude')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of latitude and longitude of airports?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd
from wordcloud import WordCloud

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    text = ' '.join(data['name'])
    wordcloud = WordCloud(background_color='white', width=800, height=800).generate(text)

    plt.imshow(wordcloud, interpolation='bilinear')
    plt.axis('off')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport names?')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.hist(data['iata'], bins=50, color='blue', alpha=0.7)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of airport codes?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Airport Codes')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
